<item>
            <title>[FLINK-5556] BarrierBuffer resets bytes written on spiller roll over</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5556</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When rolling over a spilled sequence of buffers, the tracker bytes written are reset to 0. They are reported to the checkpoint listener right after this operation, which results in the reported buffered bytes always being 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13035917">FLINK-5556</key>
            <summary>BarrierBuffer resets bytes written on spiller roll over</summary>
